```class Solution {
public:
    int repeatedStringMatch(string a, string b) {
        string temp = a;
        int count = 1;
        while (temp.size() < b.size()) {
            temp += a;
            count++;
        }
        if (temp.find(b) != string::npos) return count;
        temp += a;
        count++;
        if (temp.find(b) != string::npos) return count;
        return -1;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution repeats string a until its length is greater than or equal to the length of string b, then checks if b is a substring of the repeated string a. If not, it repeats a one more time and checks again. If still not, it returns -1.

